article.description: Temple beats Penn 76-67 for Big 5 win
article.headline: Temple beats Penn 76-67 for Big 5 win
article.linkText: Temple beats Penn 76-67 for Big 5 win
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Mark Williams scored a career-high 24 points and Temple defeated Penn 76-67 for a Big 5 victory on Tuesday night. Will Cummings scored 16 points, and had seven rebounds and five assists for the Owls (3-2). Quenton DeCosey added 14 points and Josh Brown 11. Tony Hicks scored 17 points for the Quakers (0-4) before fouling out with 6:30 left. Matt Howard scored 15 and Darien Nelson-Henry 12, along with grabbing eight rebounds. Penn held a 37-29 advantage on the boards but had 19 turnovers. Temple led 44-37 at halftime and went up 11 early in the second half on a 3-pointer by Williams. Penn closed to within a point at 61-60 and was down only 70-67 with 1:15 remaining before the Owls hit their free throws down the stretch. Temple bounced back after losses to Duke and UNLV.
